cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object categorization from RGB-D data using convolutional neural networks. The use of synthetic data also suggests a possible connection to robotics (cs.RO) as synthetic data can be used to train robots in simulation before deploying them in the real world. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper could also be related to graphics (cs.GR) as it involves the generation of synthetic images.
